text: Just tried Yong Le Restaurantâ€™s chicken chop rice. Incredibly juicy, tasty and yummy with complimentary thick & creamy tomyum soup for dipping. The steamed rice was soft and appetising, such a perfect match while eating with the chicken chop. The price is reasonable and worthy for the yummy food. Highly recommended.

Open air traditional Zi char
Can park opposite or three car parks next door.
The food was good! The cereal prawn was sweet and salty super addictive. Ordered the claypot tofu as well, it was delicious.

Pleasantly surprised by this yummy Yuzu squid! Not a dish in the menu but just asked the chef for daily specials, leave it to the kitchen to whip up something. This tze char plc is indeed a hidden gem for sure!

Their claypot rice is one of the best i ever had. Came here just for this.
Definitely worth recommending.
